******
[3] China
Date: 19 Feb 2004
From: ProMED-mail promed@promedmail.org

Source: Xinhua [edited]


3 previously suspected outbreaks of the H5N1 strain of bird flu
have been confirmed by the National Avian Influenza Reference
Laboratory, the Ministry of Agriculture announced Thursday. The
bird flu infected regions are Huanggang City of Hubei and
Chenzhou City of Hunan, 2 provinces in the south China area, and
Baicheng City in northeastern China's Jilin Province.

The local government has taken measures against the disease by
culling poultry in the affected areas and imposing prompt quarantine
restrictions, said the ministry.

At the same time, the reference laboratory excluded 3 previously
suspected outbreaks reported in Anning and Xigu districts and
Jingyuan County of Lanzhou City in northwestern China's Gansu
Province, according to the ministry.

